The soundtrack was composed by Makoto Yoshimori, who captures the high-swinging Jazz of the time period with grace and intensity. There aren't a lot of tracks on the soundtrack, but everything that is there fits with the show's sense and style perfectly. The OP is a MASTERPIECE, while the ED is alright. I don't know how the Japanese voice acting is, but the English dub is probably the best dub I've heard. The accents are ON POINT for every character, and are masterfully done.\
